<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,222,1222]" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,763,789]" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The species has a much slower echeme repetition rate than the other species of the subgroup (echeme periods about 3 s; 
<tableCitation box="[356,429,799,825]" captionStart="TABLE 4" captionStartId="8.[148,236,530,556]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="TABLE 4. Song parameters in the confracta subgroup." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF55663AFFB4777FFF4CFD9FFD40947A" pageId="25" pageNumber="126" tableUuid="DF55663AFFB4777FFF4CFD9FFD40947A">Tab. 4</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="126" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,222,1222]" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,835,861]" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Description.</emphasis>
Morphologically no difference to other species of the 
<taxonomicName box="[995,1144,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Mecopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confracta">
<emphasis box="[995,1144,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">M. confracta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup (Liu Cx 
<emphasis box="[1376,1437,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">et al.</emphasis>
2020).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,222,1222]" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,374,907,933]" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Measurements</emphasis>
(in mm): 
<collectingCountry box="[494,534,907,933]" name="Switzerland" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">CH</collectingCountry>
3738, 3746: pronotum length 8.0–8.7; tegmen length 55–57; tegmen width 13; hind femora length 42.0–44.5.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,222,1222]" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">
In peninsular 
<collectingCountry box="[352,457,979,1005]" name="Malaysia" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
, the species is often found syntopically with 
<taxonomicName box="[959,1100,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Mecopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="himalaya">
<emphasis box="[959,1100,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">M. himalaya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(our data, 
<bibRefCitation author="Tan, M. K. &amp; Kamaruddin, K." pageId="25" pageNumber="126" pagination="21 - 40" refId="ref26617" refString="Tan, M. K. &amp; Kamaruddin, K. M (2016) A contribution to the knowledge of Orthoptera diversity from Peninsular Malaysia: Bukit Larut, Perak. Zootaxa, 4111 (1), 21 - 40. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4111.1.2" type="journal article" year="2016">Tan &amp; Kamaruddin 2016</bibRefCitation>
). It is typically a little bit smaller than 
<taxonomicName box="[644,748,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Mecopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="himalaya">
<emphasis box="[644,748,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">himalaya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and often brown, whereas 
<taxonomicName box="[1052,1156,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Mecopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="himalaya">
<emphasis box="[1052,1156,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">himalaya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is more often green.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,222,1222]" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,379,1051,1077]" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Chromosomes:</emphasis>
2n = 29, FN = 52; pairs 1 metacentric and 4–7, 9, 10, 12–14 metacentric/ submetacentric, 3 subacrocentric, 2, 8 and 11 acrocentric, X chromosome submetacentric (
<figureCitation box="[961,1044,1087,1114]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1235,1259]" captionTargetBox="[261,1329,186,1204]" captionTargetId="figure-19@27.[249,1338,181,1210]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 15. C-banded karyotypes (left side) and mitotic metaphase (right side) of five Mecopoda species with different chromosome number (2n). Karyotypes are reconstructed by arranging homologous chromosomes in order of decreasing size. X, sex chromosome." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5141316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5141316/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="126" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,222,1222]" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,422,1123,1149]" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">Derivatio nominis.</emphasis>
Named in honour of Enrico Sismondo who discovered the song diversity of 
<emphasis box="[1311,1436,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serville" authorityYear="1831" box="[1311,1432,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Mecopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Mecopoda</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
collected and recorded the 
<typeStatus box="[459,507,1160,1186]" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">type</typeStatus>
specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heller &amp; Baker &amp; Ingrisch &amp; Korsunovskaya &amp; Liu &amp; Riede &amp; Warchałowska-Šliwa" authorityYear="2021" box="[673,826,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Mecopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sismondoi">
<emphasis box="[673,826,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="126">M. sismondoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and analyzed and described the signal interactions in that genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Sismondo, E" box="[280,461,1195,1221]" pageId="25" pageNumber="126" pagination="55 - 58" refId="ref26341" refString="Sismondo, E (1990) Synchronous, alternating, and phase-locked stridulation by a tropical katydid. Science, 249, 55 - 58. https: // doi. org / 10.1126 / science. 249.4964.55" type="journal article" year="1990">Sismondo 1990</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
